cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the Signal to Interference plus Noise Ratio (SINR), which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the improvement of quality of service (QoS), which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions interference mitigation, which is a security concern in wireless networks. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an approach to improve the performance of wireless networks, which can be seen as a control problem.
